    stem: `A 56-year-old man presents with complaints of 10 kg weight loss in the past three months and jaundice. He denies any abdominal pain, but he describes symptoms of early satiety. Recently, he has noticed dark urine and pale stool. On examination, he has icteric sclera and a palpable right upper quadrant mass that moves with respiration. No abdominal tenderness is elicited. Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial investigation?`,
