    subtopic: "Liver hemangioma",
    stem: `A 66-year-old man presents with intermittent right upper quadrant pain. An ultrasound, performed to reveal the cause of gallstones, reveals a lesion in the liver. A triple-phase CT scan is performed for more evaluation, showing a 35 mm subcortical lesion with early prominent dense enhancement, which spreads through the lesion in the late portal venous phase. Which one of the following conditions would fit this description best?`,
