    stem: `A 27-year-old woman of Jewish descent presents with jaundice for the last week. She reports recently "battling a stubborn cold" and sometimes has abdominal pain. She has no other complaints; her medical history is only significant for chronic rhinosinusitis. Laboratory studies reveal the following: Total bilirubin 62 μmol/L (3-17); Indirect bilirubin 2 μmol (1.7-5); Aspartate aminotransferase (AST) 22 U/L (8-48); Alanine aminotransferase (ALT) 21 U/L (7-55); Alkaline phosphatase 64 U/L (40-129). After a thorough chart review, it was discovered she had a liver biopsy performed 3 years before her visit, which revealed black granular pigment in the majority of hepatocytes. Which of the following is the most likely diagnosis?`,
