    stem: `A 57-year-old man presents to your GP clinic with complaints of dysphagia and hoarseness. The first symptom was hoarseness, which started almost one month ago, followed by the development of dysphagia after 2 weeks. His past medical history is significant for surgery for achalasia 10 years ago. On examination, normal-appearing but paralyzed vocal cords are noted. A CT scan is arranged that shows a mass in the thoracic inlet. Which one of the following could be the most likely diagnosis?`,
