    stem: `A 39-year-old Aboriginal man presents to your practice with a 6-week history of abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, and bowel motions that are difficult to flush down the toilet. The abdominal pain is described as a constant and disabling radiating to the back. The pain is neither brought up nor alleviated by eating. He is a chronic alcoholic and continues to drink alcohol in large amounts. Which one of the following investigations is most likely to reveal the underlying cause of his symptoms?`,
